docs.description: Computer Vision System Laboratories Corp. (Computer Vision) is a development-stage company. Computer Vision is engaged in the development of products intended for medical uses. The Company is focused on developing two products, which includes the Sentinel BreastScan System and a patent maneuverable-coiled guidewire. The Sentinel BreastScan is designed to be a non-invasive screening system that serves as an adjunct to conventional breast cancer detection modalities, including Clinical Breast Examination (CBE), which provides information to doctors on overall breast health. The Sentinel BreastScan develops high resolution digital infrared imaging intended to aid in the detection of breast cancer. During the fiscal year ending December 31, 2011 (fiscal 2011), the Company fabricated its coiled guidewire in cooperation with Custom Wire Technologies, a guidewire fabrication company. As of December 31, 2011, the Company had not generated any revenue from its operations.
docs.name: Computer Vis Sys Lab (CVSL)

docs.description: iShares Global Clean Energy ETF, formerly iShares S&P Global Clean Energy Index Fund (the Fund), is an exchange-traded fund. The Fund seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the S&P Global Clean Energy Index. The S&P Global Clean Energy Index includes clean energy production companies, clean energy equipment and technology providers. The Fund operates in a range of sectors, which include electric utilities, semiconductors and semiconductor equipment, independent power producers and energy traders, commercial services and supplies, and electrical equipment. BlackRock Fund Advisors acts as an investment adviser.

docs.description: Retail Estates SA is a Belgium-based company, which invests in real estate. The Company focuses on retail properties located on the periphery of residential areas or along access roads to urban centers, mainly in the Flemish and Wallonia Regions of Belgium. It buys properties from third parties, or builds and markets shop premises on its own account. The properties are between 500 and 3,000 square meters, and a typical retail property has an average area of 1,000 square meters. The Company's tenants include such retail chains, ad Brantano NV, Piocheur NV, Blokker groep, FUN, Carpetright and Krefel, among others. As of March 31, 2012, the Company had 451 premises in its portfolio. The total lettable are of its properties amounts to 428,548 square meters.
docs.name: Retail Estates NV (RET)

docs.description: Deutsche Post AG is a Germany-based logistics services provider. The Company operates four main business divisions: Mail; Express; Global Forwarding, Freight, and Supply Chain. The Mail business division comprises the transport and delivery of written communications and serves as an end-to-end service provider for the management of written communications. The Express business division offers international and domestic courier and express services to business and private customers. The Global Forwarding, Freight business division comprises the transportation of goods by rail, road, air and sea. The Supply Chain business division is engaged in contract logistics and provides warehousing and transport services, as well as services along the entire supply chain in the different sectors. The Company diversifies its activities into geographical areas, including Germany, rest of Europe, the Americas, Asia Pacific and Other regions.
docs.name: Deutsche Post AG ADR (DPSGY)
